			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ahem...I at this point am a level 22 Erudite Magician and I glad that I am.  Living in Toxx is a pain and if you can't stand the dark, just head over to Qeynos.  I think our Higher Intelligence is more important then Infravison or most other skills.  Since Intellgence determine the amount of mana we have (((INT/5)+2)*LEVEL) it is very import and you will find that at high levels inteligence boosting items are more important then mana.  Example is the skull of Gen`tra which grants 20 mana. Big deal! That is one summon food spell almost for me.  When you get high and your damage spells cost 105 mana to cast, that extra intel is important.  As I understand it wizard damage spells cost a bunch more so that mana is important. Anyways about the infravison I know that enchanters and magicians have ways around it. And enchanters also have ways to change their apperance to get better prices(lucky bums :)  And wizards can teleport them selves around the world so they can just go back home and sell(lucky again).  But us magicians have our little pets so I guees it balance out. And the necros are going to get their own zone in a few months I hear so they have a good reason to be an erudite as well.  I will also agree about the Paladins having their skills raise quicker becuase of the intelligence.  I remeber playing a barbarian warrior and it was hella tuff gett that slashing skill up compared to my mage that can get his magic skill uped in a couple of casts.   And never get too bummed about the other races, just try to stick to it and you will survive this world.  On the sever I play on, Erudites are a rarity but when we run into each other, we always have a laugh about other races and then will can blast some stuff.  Just to give you an idea, a wizard and I both took on things by ourselves that were 4 or 5 levels higher then us just by using our spells!  And don't forget you will be the envy of any group when you can...*cough*...borrow a kill from so low lifes that think that they can take a monster you wanted(valuable in high pass).  I still know a bunch of Erudites that started characters the same time I did.  We always sit back and talk about the good fun days at Kerra Isle where we would get destroyed by the masses of kerrans that were there.  And we have all vowed to go back and teach mitty a leason about abusing Erudites.  Well thats all I have to say about the Erudites.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
